          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Clarence Place</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>30 May /47</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>My Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I return you many<lb/> thanks for your last
                                        kind<lb/> favor. The bill on <date>10th</date> [?]<lb/> for
                                        £11..7..10–which she has<lb/> accepted. I promised to
                                        refund<lb/> to me tomorrow– This must<lb/> I fear be a very
                                        brief little<lb/> satisfactory epistle, for I am<lb/> much
                                        hurried, from long<lb/> continued indisposition
                                        correspondence<lb/> has been is a great fatigue<lb/> but I
                                        am anxious to acknowledge</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>your remittance I explained<lb/> that my last work "House<lb/>
                                        Influence a Sale for Mothers and daughters" is <hi
                                                  rend="underline">not</hi> published<lb/> at my own
                                        expense–The profits<lb/> whatever they may be are to<lb/> be
                                        divided between my<lb/> publisher (who has taken the<lb/>
                                        whole risk) myself–therefore<lb/> I should be glad if they
                                        book could<lb/> get a circulation in
                                                  <placeName>America</placeName><lb/> but I could
                                        not send them<lb/> out. <persName>Mrssrs Carey
                                                  Hart</persName>, if<lb/> they <hi rend="underline"
                                                  >really</hi> wish for theirs<lb/> must write
                                        themselves to<lb/>
                                        <persName>Miss Greenbridge</persName> Sons<lb/>
                                        <placeName>5 Patornostor low Cheapside<lb/>
                                                  London</placeName>– their order will<lb/> of
                                        course be attended to<lb/> I will enclose with this</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>some notices of the<lb/> work which have been printed<lb/> on my
                                        publishers monthly<lb/> lists of <date>May</date>
                                        <date>June</date>, which<lb/> will give you an idea how<lb/>
                                        favorably it has been received<lb/> by the English
                                        generally. I<lb/> do not near[?] my own people<lb/> for I
                                        would never publish<lb/> a work of general storation<lb/>
                                        depending on <hi rend="underline">their</hi> support.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My Jewish Faith has<lb/> here received with
                                        much<lb/> encouragement by the Jews in<lb/>
                                        <placeName>England</placeName>– started[?] to land<lb/> so
                                        very high as an useful<lb/> work for the proper [?]<lb/> if
                                        our Holy Faith effectual<lb/> guard against the [?]</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>Christianity, that I cannot<lb/> but believe it will be
                                        received<lb/> with the same favor by my<lb/> Jewish friends
                                        in <placeName>America</placeName> You would<lb/> oblige me
                                        very much by<lb/> informing <persName>Mr Mrs
                                                  Cohen</persName> of [?]<lb/> of the work for I am
                                        about<lb/> starting for <placeName>Germany</placeName> next<lb/>
                                        <date>Tuesday</date> evening, I cannot<lb/> spare time to
                                        write to them<lb/> myself. We expect to be<lb/> absent from
                                                  <placeName>England</placeName> till<lb/> the
                                        beginning or end of <date>September</date><lb/> consequently
                                        you will not be<lb/> surprised even if you should<lb/> have
                                        occasion to write on [?]<lb/> to me–at not receiving
                                        any<lb/> communication from me till<lb/> my return. I have
                                        nearly<lb/> forgotten to say I had <hi rend="underline">no
                                                  intentions</hi><lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">whatever</hi> of having a second
                                        edition<lb/> of the "[?] of <placeName>Israel</placeName>"
                                        printed<lb/> in <placeName>America</placeName>. I only asked
                                        the</p>
                              <pb n="5"/>
                              <p>cost from curiosity. I could get it<lb/> reprinted for somewhat
                                        less than your<lb/> stated sum in
                                                  <placeName>England</placeName>, therefore
                                        should<lb/> never think of restoring or [?] a<lb/>
                                        speculation in <placeName>America</placeName>. With<lb/>
                                        many thanks for all your friendly<lb/> exertions in my favor
                                        I remain</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">Yours truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">
                                        <persName role="author">Grace Aguilar</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>I hope your health is improving</p>
                    </body>
